---
import { Markdown } from 'astro/components';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const projects = [
  {
    title: 'Autograph',
    description: 'A cryptographic protocol designed to help give people agency over their digital lives.',
    url: 'https://autograph.sh'
  },
  {
    title: 'Stedy',
    description: 'A JavaScript development kit with focus on simplicity and flexibility.',
    url: 'https://github.com/christoffercarlsson/stedy'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="👋🏻">
  <div class="intro">
    <Markdown>
      # Imagine a world where each of us have the freedom to define life on our own terms...

    - We control our **identity**. Each of us decide who we are and how we present
      ourselves to the world.
    - We have **true ownership**. We are in control of our personal information and
      belongings - where and how they are kept, and who we share them with.
    - We have complete freedom to choose who we **trust** and **collaborate** with.
    - We communicate **freely** and **privately** without being monitored.
    - Each of us have **equal opportunity** to make an impact.
    - We **respect** and **take care** of each other and the world that we live in.

    <img id="portrait" src="/cc.jpeg" alt="CC" align="left" />

    👋 Hey, I'm Chris. By helping to build the tools that we need to **thrive in a
    free society**, I hope to contribute to this vision of the future.

      On this site I share thoughts and ideas, projects that I'm working on, and
      things that I've learned.

      If you want to get in touch you can
      [send me an email](mailto:cc@christofferc.com) (you can encrypt your message
      using my [PGP public key](https://christofferc.com/cc.asc)).
    </Markdown>
  </div>
  <hr />
  <h2>Projects</h2>
  {projects.map((project) => (
    <>
      <h3>
        <a href={project.url}>{project.title}</a>
      </h3>
      <p>{project.description}</p>
    </>
  ))}
</BaseLayout>
